com.topcoder.shared.netCommon
Interface CSReader

All Known Implementing Classes:
CSHandler
public interface CSReader

This interface is used for reading bytes from a binary stream and reconstructing from them data in Java primitive types, selected Java Collections types and CustomSerializable instances. Usually java.io.DataInput is used for reading primitive types and the CustomSerializable.customReadObject method is used for reading custom classes.

Author:
Timur Zambalayev
See Also:
CSWriter, CustomSerializable, DataInput
